<inglise>(Applicable as of 01.01.1997 pursuant to 11.06.97 entered into force 10.07.97 - RT I 1997, 48, 776; 17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Oma asukohariigis k&auml;ibemaksukohustuslasena registreeritud vastava riigi residentidele tagastatakse rahandusministri kehtestatud tingimustel ja korras Eestis soetatud nende mitteresidentide Eestis teostatava tegevusega seotud kaupade ja teenuste ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaks, kui nende ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu on Eestis registreeritud maksukohustuslastel vastavalt k&auml;esolevale seadusele &otilde;igus enda maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaksust maha arvata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) (4) The value added tax which non-residents who in their respective home countries are registered as persons liable to value added tax pay in Estonia upon purchase of goods and services relating to the activities carried out by such non-residents in Estonia shall be refunded under the conditions and pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance if, pursuant to this Act, the taxable persons registered in Estonia have the right to deduct the value added tax paid upon the purchase of such goods and services from the value added tax calculated on their taxable supply. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibemaks tagastatakse nende riikide residentidele, kus Eesti ettev&otilde;tjatele kaupade ja teenuste ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu tagastatakse tingimusel, et nendel mitteresidentidel ei ole Eestis filiaali ega Maksuameti kohalikus asutuses registreeritud p&uuml;sivat tegevuskohta v&otilde;i kui vastavate kaupade ja teenuste soetamine ei ole mitteresidendi filiaali v&otilde;i Eestis asuva p&uuml;siva tegevuskohaga seotud. </eesti>
<inglise>Value added tax shall be refunded to the residents of such countries in which the value added tax paid by Estonian undertakings upon the purchase of goods and services is refunded, on the condition that such non-residents do not have a branch in Estonia or a permanent establishment registered in a local Tax Board office, or if the purchase of the corresponding goods or services is not related to the non-resident's branch or permanent establishment in Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (1)) K&auml;ibemaks tagastatakse rahandusministri kehtestatud vormis esitatud taotluses nimetatud pangakontole. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (1)) A value added tax refund is transferred to a bank account specified in an application submitted in the format established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui pangakonto on avatud v&auml;ljaspool Eesti tolliterritooriumi asuvas krediidiasutuses, katab raha&uuml;lekandega seotud kulud k&auml;ibemaksu tagastamise taotleja. </eesti>
<inglise>If a bank account is opened in a credit institution outside the Estonian customs territory, the expenses relating to the transfer shall be covered by the person applying for the refund of value added tax. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (2)) Rahandusministril on &otilde;igus kehtestada kaupade ja teenuste loetelu, mille soetamisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu mitteresidentidele ei tagastata, kuigi Eestis registreeritud maksukohustuslastel on &otilde;igus nende kaupade ja teenuste ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu enda maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaksust maha arvata. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (2)) The Minister of Finance has the right to establish a list of goods and services the value added tax paid upon the purchase of which shall not be refunded to non-residents even though the taxable persons registered in Estonia have the right to deduct the value added tax paid upon the purchase of such goods and services from the value added tax calculated on their taxable supply. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Vabariigi Valitsus v&otilde;ib kehtestada soodustusi k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud isikutele ja asutustele nende poolt kaupade ja teenuste ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu tagastamisel tingimusel, et v&auml;lisriigis on tagatud samad soodustused Eesti vastavatele isikutele ja asutustele. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) The Government of the Republic may establish incentives for the refund of value added tax paid by persons and agencies specified in subsection (1) of this section upon the purchase of goods and services, on the condition that the same incentives are guaranteed to the corresponding Estonian persons and agencies in the foreign state. </inglise>
<eesti>(08.10.97 j&otilde;ust.06.11.97 - RT I 1997, 74, 1231) </eesti>
<inglise>(08.10.97 entered into force 06.11.97 - RT I 1997, 74, 1231) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 15. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 15. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibe toimumise aeg </eesti>
<inglise>Time of supply </inglise>
<eesti>(1) V&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. ja 3. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatu, loetakse k&auml;ibe toimumise ajaks k&auml;esolevas seaduses varaseim hetkest, mil sooritati &uuml;ks allj&auml;rgnevaist toiminguist: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act but excluding the provisions of subsections (2) and (3) of this section, the time of supply is deemed to be the earliest moment at which one of the following acts is performed: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kauba ostjale, vahendajale v&otilde;i komisjon&auml;rile l&auml;hetamine v&otilde;i k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemine v&otilde;i teenuse osutamine; </eesti>
<inglise>1) dispatch or making available of a good to a purchaser, intermediary or broker, or provision of a service; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>2) kauba v&otilde;i teenuse eest arve v&auml;ljastamine; </eesti>
<inglise>2) issue of an invoice for a good or service; </inglise>
<eesti>3) kauba v&otilde;i teenuse eest maksmine; </eesti>
<inglise>3) payment for a good or service; </inglise>
<eesti>4) kauba v&otilde;i teenuse tarbimine maksukohustuslase enda poolt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 3 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud juhtudel; </eesti>
<inglise>4) consumption of a good or service by a taxable person, in the cases provided for in subsection 3 (2) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) (Kehtetu - 09.10.97 j&otilde;ust.06.11.97 - RT I 1997, 74, 1232) </eesti>
<inglise>5) (Repealed - 09.10.97 entered into force 06.11.1997 - RT I 1997, 74, 1232) </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Samale ostjale regulaarselt v&otilde;i pidevalt v&otilde;&otilde;randatavate kaupade ja teenuste puhul, mis on nimetatud rahandusministri poolt kehtestatud loetelus, loetakse k&auml;ibe toimumise ajaks kauba l&auml;hetamise v&otilde;i ostjale k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemise v&otilde;i teenuse osutamise kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In the case of regular or constant transfers of goods or services specified in a list established by the Minister of Finance to the same purchaser, the time of supply is deemed to be the month in which the goods are dispatched or made available to the purchaser, or the services are provided. </inglise>
<eesti>Kinnis- ja vallasvara kasutusrendile ning kauba kapitalirendile andmisel loetakse k&auml;ibe toimumise ajaks kauba v&otilde;i vara rentimise iga kuu. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case of an operating lease of immovable or movable property or financial lease of goods, the time of supply is deemed to be each month during which the goods or property are leased. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Juhul kui m&otilde;ni k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ike punktides 1-3 nimetatud toiming oli sooritatud enne k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 10 s&auml;testatud kohustuste tekkimist, peab registreeritud maksukohustuslane arvestama tehingu maksustatavalt v&auml;&auml;rtuselt k&auml;ibemaksu vaid juhul, kui kauba l&auml;hetamine v&otilde;i ostjale k&auml;ttesaadavaks tegemine v&otilde;i teenuse osutamine toimus eelnimetatud kohustuste kehtimise ajal. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If any of the acts specified in clauses (1) 1) -3) of this section are performed before the duties provided for in &sect; 10 of this Act arise, a registered taxable person is required to calculate value added tax on the taxable value of the transaction only if the goods are dispatched or made available to the purchaser or the services are provided during the period in which such duties apply to the taxable person. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(3 (1)) Teiselt registreeritud maksukohustuslaselt kasvava metsa raie&otilde;iguse, metsamaterjali, saematerjali v&otilde;i nende materjalide transpordi- ja valmistamisteenuste ostmisel loetakse k&auml;ive toimunuks raie&otilde;iguse, metsamaterjali, saematerjali v&otilde;i nende materjalide transpordi- ja valmistamisteenuste eest arve k&auml;ttesaamisel. </eesti>
<inglise>(3 (1)) In the case of the purchase of a right to cut standing crop, of timber, sawn timber or the transport and manufacturing services of the timber from another registered taxable person, supply is deemed to take place upon the receipt of the invoice for the right to cut standing crop, the timber, sawn timber or the transport and manufacturing services of the timber. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823; 06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 26, 148) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823; 06.03.2001 entered into force 01.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 26, 148) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Impordi puhul loetakse maksustatav k&auml;ive toimunuks kauba saabumisel Eesti tolliterritooriumile v&otilde;i selle vabastamisel esialgsest tolliprotseduurist, kui kaup suunatakse tolliseaduses s&auml;testatud korras vabasse ringlusse. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In the case of imports, the taxable supply is deemed to take place upon the entry of the goods into the Estonian customs territory or upon the release thereof from the preliminary customs procedure if the goods are released for free circulation pursuant to the procedure provided for in the Customs Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Kui k&auml;ibe toimumise ajaks on hetk, mil toimus kauba v&otilde;i teenuse eest maksmine, toimub k&auml;ibemaksu arvestamine rahandusministri poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) If the time of supply is the moment of payment for goods or services, value added tax shall be calculated pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 16. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 16. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibe toimumise koht </eesti>
<inglise>Place of supply </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibe toimumise koht on Eesti, kui: </eesti>
<inglise>The place of supply is Estonia if: </inglise>
<eesti>1) kaup imporditakse Eestisse, toimetatakse saajale v&otilde;i tehakse talle k&auml;ttesaadavaks Eestis v&otilde;i eksporditakse Eestist; </eesti>
<inglise>1) the goods are imported into Estonia, delivered or made available to the recipient in Estonia, or exported from Estonia; </inglise>
<eesti>2) teenust osutava isiku ettev&otilde;tlus toimub Eestis v&otilde;i teenuse osutajaks on Eestis registreeritud ettev&otilde;tja v&otilde;i muu juriidiline isik, v&auml;lja arvatud rahandusministri poolt m&auml;&auml;ratud juhud. </eesti>
<inglise>2) the person providing a service engages in enterprise in Estonia or the provider of the service is an undertaking or other legal person registered in Estonia, except in the cases specified by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 17. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 17. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksustamisperiood ja k&auml;ibedeklaratsioon </eesti>
<inglise>Taxable period and value added tax return </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Eestis vabas ringluses olevate kaupade ja Eestis osutatud teenuste k&auml;ibe puhul on k&auml;ibemaksuga maksustamise periood kalendrikuu. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of the supply of goods in free circulation in Estonia and services provided in Estonia, the taxable period for value added tax shall be one calendar month. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaupade impordil toimub k&auml;ibemaksuga maksustamine tollieeskirjadega impordimaksude tasumiseks s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the import of goods, value added tax shall be imposed pursuant to the procedure for payment of import charges provided by the customs rules. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuamet v&otilde;ib maksukohustuslasele kehtestada kalendrikuust erineva maksustamisperioodi. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The Tax Board may establish a taxable period other than one calendar month for a taxable person. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;ibedeklaratsioon esitatakse maksustamisperioodile j&auml;rgneva kuu 20. kuup&auml;evaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Value added tax returns shall be submitted by the twentieth day of the month following the taxable period. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 2. l&otilde;ikele on maksukohustuslasele kehtestatud kalendrikuust erinev maksustamisperiood, m&auml;&auml;rab k&auml;ibedeklaratsiooni esitamise t&auml;htaja Maksuamet. </eesti>
<inglise>If a taxable period other than one calendar month is established for a taxable person pursuant to subsection (2) of this section, the due date for the submission of value added tax returns shall be specified by the Tax Board. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) &Uuml;he maksukohustuslasena registreeritud isikud esitavad k&auml;ibedeklaratsioonid eraldi, kuid vastutavad k&auml;ibemaksu t&auml;htaegse tasumise eest solidaarselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Persons registered as a single taxable person shall submit value added tax returns separately but are solidarily liable for payment of value added tax by the due date. </inglise>
<eesti>&Uuml;he maksukohustuslasena registreerimise otsuse kehtetuks tunnistamise korral vastutavad maksukohustuslased solidaarselt k&auml;ibemaksuv&otilde;la eest, mis tekkis maksustamisperioodil, mil nad olid registreeritud &uuml;he maksukohustuslasena. </eesti>
<inglise>In the case the decision concerning registration as a single taxable person is annulled, the taxable persons shall be solidarily liable for the value added tax arrears which arose during the taxable periods in which they were registered as a single taxable person </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Eelmiste maksustamisperioodide kohta esitatud k&auml;ibedeklaratsioonide andmete muutmisel on registreeritud maksukohustuslane kohustatud esitama Maksuametile vastava maksustamisperioodi kohta uue, muudetud andmetega k&auml;ibedeklaratsiooni. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Upon the amendment of information submitted in a value added tax return concerning a previous taxable period, a registered taxable person is required to submit a new value added tax return with amended information to the Tax Board concerning the corresponding taxable period. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 18. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 18. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasumisele kuuluva maksusumma arvutamine </eesti>
<inglise>Calculation of amount of tax due </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Registreeritud maksukohustuslase poolt tasumisele kuuluv k&auml;ibemaks on k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 13 nimetatud maksum&auml;&auml;ra j&auml;rgi maksustamisperioodi maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaks, millest on maha arvatud maksustamisperioodil: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) The value added tax to be paid by a registered taxable person is the value added tax calculated on taxable supply during a taxable period according to the tax rates specified in &sect; 13 of this Act, from which the following has been deducted: </inglise>
<eesti>1) teistelt registreeritud maksukohustuslastelt soetatud ning oma ettev&otilde;tluses kasutatavate kaupade ja teenuste eest tasumisele kuuluv k&auml;ibemaks; </eesti>
<inglise>1) value added tax paid for goods and services which are purchased from other registered taxable persons during the taxable period and which are used for the purposes of enterprise; </inglise>
<eesti>2) oma ettev&otilde;tluseks imporditud kaupadelt tasutud k&auml;ibemaks. </eesti>
<inglise>2) value added tax paid during the taxable period on goods imported for the purposes of enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Kaupade ja teenuste kasutamisega ettev&otilde;tluses v&otilde;rdsustatakse ka kaupade ja teenuste tarbimine maksukohustuslase enda poolt k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 3 2. l&otilde;ikes nimetatud juhtudel. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The consumption of goods or services by a taxable person in the cases specified in subsection 3 (2) of this Act is deemed to be equal to the use of goods or services for the purposes of enterprise. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Kui registreeritud maksukohustuslane kasutab kaupa v&otilde;i teenust nii ettev&otilde;tluses v&otilde;i sellega v&otilde;rdsustatud oma tarbimises kui ka omatarbeks muudel juhtudel, kuulub vastava kauba v&otilde;i teenuse soetamisel makstud k&auml;ibemaks mahaarvamisele rahandusministri poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) If a registered taxable person uses goods or services both for the purposes of enterprise or consumption equivalent thereto and for self-consumption in other cases, the value added tax paid upon the purchase of the corresponding goods or services shall be deducted pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(3 (1)) Kasvava metsa raie&otilde;iguse, metsamaterjali, saematerjali v&otilde;i nende materjalide transpordi- ja valmistamisteenuste m&uuml;&uuml;misel registreeritud maksukohustuslase poolt teisele registreeritud maksukohustuslasele tasub tehingu kohta esitatud arvel n&auml;idatud k&auml;ibemaksu ostja, makstes m&uuml;&uuml;jale m&uuml;&uuml;gihinna ilma k&auml;ibemaksuta. </eesti>
<inglise>(3 (1)) Upon the sale of a right to cut standing crop, of timber, sawn timber or the transport and manufacturing services of the timber by one registered taxable person to another registered taxable person, the value added tax specified in the invoice concerning the transaction shall be paid by the purchaser and the purchaser shall pay to the seller only the selling price without the value added tax. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibemaksu mahaarvamine raie&otilde;iguse, metsamaterjali, saematerjali v&otilde;i nende materjalide transpordi- ja valmistamisteenuste ostmise korral toimub k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>Upon the purchase of a right to cut standing crop, of timber, sawn timber or the transport and manufacturing services of the timber, the value added tax is deducted pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823; 06.03.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 26, 148) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823; 06.03.2001 entered into force 01.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 26, 148) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaksust ei arvata maha k&auml;ibemaksu, mille registreeritud maksukohustuslane on maksnud: </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Value added tax paid by a registered taxable person shall not be deducted from value added tax calculated on taxable supply: </inglise>
<eesti>1) k&uuml;laliste vastuv&otilde;tul ning oma t&ouml;&ouml;tajate toitlustamisel ja majutamisel kasutatud kaupade ja teenuste eest tasumisel; </eesti>
<inglise>1) upon payment for goods or services used for the purposes of the reception of guests or provision of meals or accommodation for the employees of the registered taxable person; </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>2) s&otilde;iduautode soetamisel ja kapitalirendile v&otilde;tmisel, samuti s&otilde;iduautode tarbeks mootorik&uuml;tuse soetamisel, v&auml;lja arvatud k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 4 (1). l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatu. </eesti>
<inglise>2) upon the purchase or financial lease of automobiles or upon the purchase of motor fuel used for automobiles, except in the cases provided for in subsection (4 (1)) of this section. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(4 (1)) Maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaksust arvatakse maha k&auml;ibemaks, mille on s&otilde;iduautode soetamisel ja kapitalirendile v&otilde;tmisel maksnud maksukohustuslane, kes tegeleb s&otilde;iduautode m&uuml;&uuml;giga v&otilde;i vallasvara kasutus- v&otilde;i kapitalirendiga ja kelle p&otilde;hikirjas on vastav tegevusala ette n&auml;htud. </eesti>
<inglise>(4 (1)) Value added tax paid upon the purchase or financial lease of automobiles by a taxable person who is engaged the sale of automobiles or in the operating or financial lease of movable property and whose articles of association prescribe such area of activity, shall be deducted from the value added tax calculated on taxable supply. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibemaks arvatakse maha tingimusel, et eelnimetatud maksukohustuslased ei v&otilde;ta m&uuml;&uuml;giks v&otilde;i rentimiseks soetatud autosid ise kasutusele. </eesti>
<inglise>Value added tax shall be deducted on the condition that such taxable persons do not use automobiles which they purchase for the purposes of sale or lease for their own purposes. </inglise>
<eesti>(24.10.96 j&otilde;ust.01.10.96 - RT I 1996, 76, 1344; 17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(24.10.96 entered into force 01.10.96 - RT I 1996, 76, 1344; 17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Maksukohustuslasel on &otilde;igus enda maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaksust maha arvata oma maksustatava k&auml;ibe tarbeks ehitatava ehitise ehitamiseks v&otilde;i remondiks soetatud kaupadelt ja teenustelt tasumisele kuuluv k&auml;ibemaks vastavalt ehitise maksustatava k&auml;ibe tarbeks kasutamise osat&auml;htsusele, samuti k&auml;ibemaksuga maksustatava ehitus- v&otilde;i remonditeenuse tarbeks soetatud kaupadelt ja teenustelt tasumisele kuuluv k&auml;ibemaks. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) A taxable person has the right to deduct the value added tax to be paid on goods and services purchased for the construction or repair of a structure constructed for the purposes of the person's taxable supply from the value added tax calculated on the person's taxable supply, according to the proportion in which the structure is used for the purposes of taxable supply; a taxable person also has the right to deduct the value added tax to be paid on goods and services purchased for the purposes of construction or repair services subject to value added tax from the value added tax calculated on the person's taxable supply. </inglise>
<eesti>Maksustatava k&auml;ibe tarbeks kasutatud hoone v&otilde;&otilde;randamisel v&otilde;i kapitalirendile andmisel viie kalendriaasta jooksul selle kasutusloa saamise aastast arvates v&otilde;i rajatise v&otilde;&otilde;randamisel v&otilde;i kapitalirendile andmisel viie kalendriaasta jooksul selle raamatupidamises arvelev&otilde;tmise aastast arvates, samuti juhul, kui hoonet hakatakse viie kalendriaasta jooksul selle kasutusloa saamise aastast arvates v&otilde;i rajatist viie kalendriaasta jooksul selle raamatupidamises arvelev&otilde;tmise aastast arvates kasutama maksuvaba k&auml;ibe tarbeks, eluruumidena v&otilde;i riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmiseks, tehakse ehitise soetusmaksumusse arvatud kaupade ja teenuste soetamisel makstud ja enda maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaksust maha arvatud k&auml;ibemaksu &uuml;mberarvestus rahandusministri kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>If a building used for the purposes of taxable supply is transferred or leased on the basis of a financial lease contract within five calendar years after the year in which the permit to use the structure was received or if a construction is transferred or leased on the basis of a financial lease contract within five years after the year in which the construction was registered in the taxable person's accounts or if within five years after the year in which the right to use a building was received or after the year in which a construction was registered in the taxable person's accounts, the building or construction is taken into use for the purposes of supply exempt for tax, as a dwelling or for the performance of the functions of the state or a local government, the value added tax which was paid upon the purchase of goods or services included in the acquisition cost of the structure and which was deducted from the value added tax calculated on the taxable supply of the taxable person shall be recalculated pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>Ehitisteks k&auml;esoleva seaduse t&auml;henduses loetakse hooneid, millele on antud kasutusluba, ja rajatisi planeerimis- ja ehitusseaduse (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 27, 380; 29, 398 ja 399; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348) t&auml;henduses. </eesti>
<inglise>For the purposes of this Act, structures are deemed to be buildings for which a permit for use has been granted and constructions as defined in the Planning and Building Act (RT I 1995, 59, 1006; 1996, 36, 738; 49, 953; 1999, 27, 380; 29, 398 and 399; 95, 843; 2000, 54, 348). </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (1)) Ehitise ehitamiseks v&otilde;i remondiks soetatud kaupadelt ja teenustelt tasumisele kuuluvat k&auml;ibemaksu ei arvata maha juhul, kui ehitist ehitatakse &uuml;hel k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 5. l&otilde;ike teises lauses nimetatud eesm&auml;rgil v&otilde;i remonditakse m&otilde;nel eespool nimetatud eesm&auml;rgil ehitatud ehitist. </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (1)) The value added tax to be paid on goods or services purchased for the construction or repair of a structure shall not be deducted if the structure is constructed for one of the purposes specified in the second sentence of subsection (5) of this section or if a structure constructed for one of the aforementioned purposes is repaired. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti ei arvata maha eluruumides kasutamiseks soetatud kaupadelt ja teenustelt tasumisele kuuluvat k&auml;ibemaksu. </eesti>
<inglise>The value added tax to be paid on goods and services purchased for the purposes of use in dwellings shall not be deducted. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(5 (2)) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 5. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud maha arvatud k&auml;ibemaksu &uuml;mberarvestust ei tehta ehitise v&otilde;&otilde;randamisel krediidi- v&otilde;i finantseerimisasutusele, kui isik, kes ehitise v&otilde;&otilde;randas, on v&otilde;tnud selle ehitise samal maksustamisperioodil, mil v&otilde;&otilde;randamine toimus, krediidi- v&otilde;i finantseerimisasutuselt kapitalirendile ja j&auml;tkab ehitise kasutamist maksustatava k&auml;ibe tarbeks samas l&otilde;ikes nimetatud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>(5 (2)) The deducted value added tax provided for in subsection (5) of this section shall not be recalculated upon transfer of a structure to a credit or financial institution if the person who transfers the structure leases the structure from the credit or financial institution on the basis of a commercial lease contract during the same period of taxation when it is transferred and continues to use the structure for the purposes of the person's taxable supply within the term specified in the same subsection. </inglise>
<eesti>(20.02.2001 j&otilde;ust.01.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 23, 129) </eesti>
<inglise>(20.02.2001 entered into force 01.04.2001 - RT I 2001, 23, 129) </inglise>
<eesti>(6) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud mahaarvamised on lubatud k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahvis 24 s&auml;testatud n&otilde;uetele vastava originaalarve v&otilde;i impordi kaubadeklaratsiooni ja kauba importimisel k&auml;ibemaksu tasumist t&otilde;endava dokumendi alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(6) The deductions provided for in subsection (1) of this section shall be permitted on the basis of an original invoice which complies with the requirements provided for in &sect; 24 of this Act, or a declaration of goods for import and a document certifying payment of value added tax upon the import of goods. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(7) K&auml;ibemaks arvatakse maha maksustamisperioodil, mil kaup v&otilde;i teenus on k&auml;tte saadud ning kauba v&otilde;i teenuse m&uuml;&uuml;jalt arve laekunud v&otilde;i k&auml;ibemaks importimisel tasutud, seejuures ei loeta k&auml;ibemaksu tasumiseks tollile tehtud ettemaksu. </eesti>
<inglise>(7) Value added tax shall be deducted during the taxable period in which the goods or services and the invoice from the seller of the goods or services are received, or in which the goods or services are received and value added tax upon import is paid; advance payments made to the customs authorities are deemed not to be payment of value added tax. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kaup saadakse k&auml;tte ning k&auml;ibemaks importimisel tasutakse erinevatel maksustamisperioodidel, arvatakse k&auml;ibemaks maha perioodil, mil m&otilde;lemad tingimused on t&auml;idetud. </eesti>
<inglise>If the goods are received and value added tax upon import is paid during different taxable periods, the value added tax shall be deducted during the period in which both conditions are fulfilled. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui kauba v&otilde;i teenuse ostmisel Eestis saadakse kaup v&otilde;i teenus ning arve kauba v&otilde;i teenuse eest k&auml;tte erinevatel maksustamisperioodidel, arvatakse k&auml;ibemaks maha maksustamisperioodil, mil kaup v&otilde;i teenus k&auml;tte saadakse, tingimusel, et arve kauba v&otilde;i teenuse eest esitatakse k&auml;esoleva seaduse paragrahv 24 7. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatud t&auml;htaja jooksul. </eesti>
<inglise>If, upon the purchase of goods or services in Estonia, goods or services and the invoice for such goods or services are received during different taxable periods, the value added tax shall be deducted during the taxable period in which the goods or services are received, on the condition that the invoice for the goods or services is submitted during the term provided for in subsection 24 (7) of this Act. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui viimatinimetatud juhul esitatakse arve hilinenult, arvatakse k&auml;ibemaks maha maksustamisperioodil, mil saadakse k&auml;tte kauba v&otilde;i teenuse kohta esitatud arve. </eesti>
<inglise>If, in the last case mentioned, the submission of the invoice is delayed, the value added tax shall be deducted during the taxable period in which the invoice submitted for the goods or services is received. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui maksukohustuslane saab kauba v&otilde;i teenuse k&auml;tte enne registreeritud maksukohustuslase &otilde;iguste ja kohustuste laienemist tema suhtes, on, s&otilde;ltumata arve esitamise ajast, lubatud k&auml;ibemaks maha arvata ainult k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect;-s 23 s&auml;testatud juhul. </eesti>
<inglise>If a taxable person receives goods or services before the rights and obligations of a registered taxable person extend to the taxable person, the value added tax is permitted to be deducted only in the case specified in &sect; 23 of this Act, regardless of the time of submission of the invoice. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845; 17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(8) K&auml;ibemaksu mahaarvamine on lubatud ainult arve originaaleksemplari alusel. </eesti>
<inglise>(8) Deduction of value added tax is permitted only on the basis of an original invoice. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui Eestis raha eest soetatud kauba v&otilde;i teenuse maksustatav v&auml;&auml;rtus &uuml;he tehingu kohta &uuml;letab 50 000 krooni, on mahaarvamine lubatud juhul, kui selle eest tasutakse t&auml;ies ulatuses krediidiasutuse kaudu kas raha&uuml;lekandega v&otilde;i sularaha sissemaksega m&uuml;&uuml;ja pangakontole. </eesti>
<inglise>If the taxable value of goods or services purchased for money in Estonia exceeds 50 000 kroons per transaction, deduction is permitted in the case the payment for the goods or services is carried out in full through a credit institution either by a bank transfer or a cash payment made to the bank account of the seller. </inglise>
<eesti>Kaupade importimisel tasutud k&auml;ibemaks on lubatud maha arvata sellest s&otilde;ltumata, kas vastava kauba soetamisel tasuti selle eest raha&uuml;lekandega v&otilde;i sularahas. </eesti>
<inglise>The value added tax paid upon importation of goods is permitted to be deducted regardless of whether the corresponding goods were paid for by a bank transfer of in cash. </inglise>
<eesti>(17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(9) Impordimaksude tasumisel Tolliameti poolt v&auml;ljaantud tunnistust omava tollimaakleri kaudu arvatakse kaupade importimisel tasutud k&auml;ibemaks maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaksust maha rahandusministri poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(9) If import charges are paid through a customs clearing agent who holds a certificate issued by the Customs Board, the value added tax paid upon the import of goods shall be deducted from the value added tax calculated on taxable supply pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(10) Kui m&uuml;&uuml;jale on ostjalt raha laekunud, kuid kauba v&otilde;i teenuse v&otilde;&otilde;randamist tegelikult ei toimu, on m&uuml;&uuml;jal lubatud t&uuml;histada k&auml;ibemaksu arvestamine sellelt kaubalt v&otilde;i teenuselt juhul, kui ta on laekunud summa ostjale tagastanud. </eesti>
<inglise>(10) If a seller receives money from a purchaser but the goods or services are not transferred, the seller is permitted to cancel the calculation of value added tax on such goods or services if the seller refunds the amount received to the purchaser. </inglise>
<eesti>Kui m&uuml;&uuml;ja on esitanud ostjale arve, kuid kauba v&otilde;i teenuse v&otilde;&otilde;randamist tegelikult ei toimu, on m&uuml;&uuml;jal lubatud teha k&auml;ibemaksu tagasiarvestus sellelt arvelt juhul, kui arve v&auml;ljakirjutamisest on m&ouml;&ouml;dunud kolm kuud, samuti juhul, kui ostja on teatanud kirjalikult kauba v&otilde;i teenuse ostmisest loobumisest. </eesti>
<inglise>If a seller submits an invoice to a purchaser but the goods or services are not transferred, the seller is permitted to make a recalculation of the value added tax with regard to the invoice if three months have passed from the issue of the invoice or if the purchaser has given written notice of renunciation of the order to purchase the goods or services. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 19. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 19. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibemaksu laekumine </eesti>
<inglise>Receipt of value added tax </inglise>
<eesti>(1) K&auml;ibemaks laekub riigieelarvesse. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Value added tax shall be paid into the state budget. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;ibemaks makstakse t&auml;iskroonides. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Value added tax shall be paid in full kroons. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 20. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 20. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibemaksu tagastamine maksukohustuslasele </eesti>
<inglise>Refund of value added tax to taxable person </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui maksustamisperioodi maksustatavalt k&auml;ibelt arvestatud k&auml;ibemaks on v&auml;iksem registreeritud maksukohustuslase poolt samal perioodil kaupade ja teenuste soetamisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu summast, tagastatakse enammakstud k&auml;ibemaks maksukohustuslasele maksukorralduse seaduse (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 2000, 45, 279; 55, 365; 84, 533, 534) paragrahvis 10 s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If value added tax calculated on taxable supply during a taxable period is less than the amount of value added tax paid by the registered taxable person upon the purchase of goods and services during the same period, the overpaid amount of value added tax shall be refunded to the taxable person pursuant to the procedure provided for in &sect; 10 of the Taxation Act (RT I 1994, 1, 5; 2000, 45, 279; 55, 365; 84; 533, 534). </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Maksuametil on &otilde;igus seoses maksukohustuslase kontrollimisega pikendada k&auml;ibemaksu tagastamise t&auml;htaega kuni 30 p&auml;eva v&otilde;rra k&auml;ibemaksu tagastamise t&auml;htp&auml;evast arvates. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) In connection with the audit of a taxable person, the Tax Board has the right to extend the term for refund of value added tax by up to thirty days from the due date for the refund of value added tax. </inglise>
<eesti>K&auml;ibemaksu tagastamise t&auml;htaja pikendamisest on Maksuamet kohustatud maksukohustuslasele teatama kirjalikult 20 p&auml;eva jooksul k&auml;ibemaksu tagastamise taotluse saamisest arvates, n&auml;idates teates &auml;ra k&auml;ibemaksu tagastamise t&auml;htaja pikendamise p&otilde;hjuse. </eesti>
<inglise>The Tax Board is required to notify the taxable person in writing of the extension of the term for refund of value added tax within twenty days after receipt of an application for the refund of value added tax, and shall indicate the reason for extension of the term for the refund of value added tax in the notice. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;ibemaksu enammakse tagastamisel &uuml;he maksukohustuslasena registreeritud maksukohustuslastele toimub enammakstud k&auml;ibemaksu arvestus k&otilde;igi nimetatud maksukohustuslaste kohta eraldi. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Upon the refund of overpaid amounts of value added tax to taxable persons registered as a single taxable person, the overpaid amounts of value added tax shall be calculated separately for each of the taxable persons. </inglise>
<eesti>Enammakstud k&auml;ibemaks tagastatakse nende maksukohustuslaste esitatud k&auml;ibedeklaratsioonide j&auml;rgi vastavalt k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi 1. ja 2. l&otilde;ikes s&auml;testatule. </eesti>
<inglise>Overpaid amounts of value added tax shall be refunded pursuant to the provisions of subsections (1) and (2) of this section on the basis of the value added tax returns submitted by such persons. </inglise>
<eesti>(19.11.98 j&otilde;ust.01.12.98 - RT I 1998, 103, 1702) </eesti>
<inglise>(19.11.98 entered into force 01.12.98 - RT I 1998, 103, 1702) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu osaline mahaarvamine </eesti>
<inglise>Partial deduction of value added tax paid upon purchase </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Kui registreeritud maksukohustuslane kasutab teistelt registreeritud maksukohustuslastelt ostetud Eestis toodetud v&otilde;i Eestisse imporditud vabas ringluses olevaid kaupu ja Eestis osutatud teenuseid v&otilde;i tema poolt imporditud kaupu nii maksustamisele kuuluva kui maksuvaba k&auml;ibe tarbeks, kuulub ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaks mahaarvamisele osaliselt. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) If a registered taxable person uses goods purchased from other registered taxable persons which are produced in Estonia or imported into Estonia and are in free circulation, or uses services purchased from other registered taxable persons and provided in Estonia, or uses goods imported by the registered taxable person for the purpose of both supply subject to taxation and exempt supply, the value added tax paid upon purchase shall be partially deducted. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(2) K&auml;ibemaksu osalisel mahaarvamisel on sama kalendriaasta jooksul lubatud kasutada kas proportsionaalse mahaarvamise meetodit v&otilde;i otsearvestuse ja proportsionaalse mahaarvamise segameetodit. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Upon the partial deduction of value added tax, either the method of proportional deduction or the method combining direct calculation and proportional deduction shall be used during the same calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>Koosk&otilde;lastatult Maksuametiga v&otilde;ib kasutada otsearvestuse ja proportsionaalse mahaarvamise segameetodi erijuhtu, mille puhul teatud tegevusvaldkonna tarbeks kaupade ja teenuste soetamisel arvatakse k&auml;ibemaks maha vastavalt registreeritud maksukohustuslase maksustatava k&auml;ibe suhtele tema kogu Eestis toimunud selle tegevusvaldkonna k&auml;ibesse. </eesti>
<inglise>With the consent of the Tax Board, a special method combining direct calculation and proportional deduction may be used, in which case, upon the purchase of goods or services necessary for certain areas of activity, the value added tax is deducted according to the proportion of the taxable supply of the registered taxable person to the supply which in such area of activity has taken place in whole Estonia. </inglise>
<eesti>Kalendriaasta l&otilde;pul tehakse k&auml;ibemaksu proportsionaalse mahaarvamise &uuml;mberarvestus vastavalt registreeritud maksukohustuslase maksustatava k&auml;ibe suhtele tema kogu Eestis toimunud k&auml;ibesse sellel kalendriaastal. </eesti>
<inglise>At the end of a calendar year, the proportional deduction of value added tax shall be recalculated according to the ratio of the taxable supply of the registered taxable person to the total supply of the taxable person in Estonia during the calendar year. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.11.96 j&otilde;ust.08.12.96 - RT I 1996, 81, 1447; 17.11.1999 j&otilde;ust.01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.11.96 entered into force 08.12.96 - RT I 1996, 81, 1447; 17.11.1999 entered into force 01.01.2000 - RT I 1999, 92, 823) </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;ibemaksu osalise mahaarvamise ning kalendriaasta l&otilde;pul &uuml;mberarvestuse tegemise ja selle k&auml;ibedeklaratsioonis kajastamise korra kehtestab rahandusminister. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The procedure for partial deduction of value added tax, recalculation of such partial deduction at the end of the calendar year and reporting thereof in a value added tax return shall be established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Koosk&otilde;lastatult Maksuametiga on isikul lubatud aasta kestel muuta ostmisel makstud k&auml;ibemaksu mahaarvamisel kasutatavat k&auml;ivete suhet. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) With the approval of the Tax Board, a person is permitted during a year to change the ratio of supply subject to taxation and supply exempt from tax used for deduction of value added tax paid upon purchase. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
<eesti>(5) Isiku ettev&otilde;tluse tarbeks p&otilde;hivara soetamisel makstud ja mahaarvatud k&auml;ibemaksusummat korrigeeritakse kolme aasta jooksul vastavalt p&otilde;hivara tegelikule maksustatava k&auml;ibe tarbeks kasutamise osat&auml;htsusele rahandusministri poolt kehtestatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(5) Amounts of value added tax paid and deducted upon the purchase of fixed assets for the purposes of enterprise by a person shall be adjusted within three years according to the actual proportion of the use of the fixed assets for the purposes of taxable supply, pursuant to the procedure established by the Minister of Finance. </inglise>
<eesti>(12.06.96 j&otilde;ust.01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </eesti>
<inglise>(12.06.96 entered into force 01.09.96 - RT I 1996, 44, 845) </inglise>
